[
    {
        "content": "<p>Code <a href=\"https://rust.docs.kernel.org/src/kernel/sync/arc.rs.html#233\">here</a>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">into_raw</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_ptr</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">core</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">mem</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">forget</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// SAFETY: The pointer is valid.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">core</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">addr_of</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">((</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>If I understand pointer provenance correctly, pointers derived from <code>addr_of!()</code> don't have the provenance for writing, therefore the result of <code>Arc::into_raw()</code> cannot be used to construct an <code>Arc</code> via <code>Arc::from_raw()</code>, right?</p>",
        "id": 492140428,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1736181642
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The docs say:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>If the place <code>expr</code> evaluates to is based on a raw pointer, then the result of <code>addr_of!</code> inherits all permissions from that raw pointer.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 492145497,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1736183314
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thank you. However, std implementation uses a <code>&amp;raw mut</code> instead of <code>&amp;raw</code>: <a href=\"https://doc.rust-lang.org/src/alloc/sync.rs.html#1581\">https://doc.rust-lang.org/src/alloc/sync.rs.html#1581</a>.</p>\n<p>And if you can recall the discussion with Ralf: <a href=\"https://rust-lang.zulipchat.com/#narrow/channel/136281-t-opsem/topic/Replacing.20.60static.20mut.60/near/465391608\">https://rust-lang.zulipchat.com/#narrow/channel/136281-t-opsem/topic/Replacing.20.60static.20mut.60/near/465391608</a></p>",
        "id": 492146324,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1736183637
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I asked Ralf to add the sentence I quoted on a PR to add the paragraph containing it.</p>",
        "id": 492146615,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1736183726
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So it means <code>addr_of!</code> should be treated as purely offset operation and that has been decided (i.e. the PR means that)?</p>",
        "id": 492146832,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1736183789
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>&lt;<a href=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/129653#discussion_r1732725767\">https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/129653#discussion_r1732725767</a>&gt;</p>",
        "id": 492146877,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1736183803
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks!</p>",
        "id": 492147210,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1736183895
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>However, I'm still not sure what we should do, we can:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Be careful and use <code>addr_of_mut!()</code> as much as possible,</li>\n<li>Embrace the future and use <code>addr_of!()</code> whenever it fits.</li>\n<li>Admit that <code>addr_of!()</code> works in cases like <code>Arc::into_raw()</code> but don't rely on it for the new code.</li>\n</ol>",
        "id": 492147845,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1736184114
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think you're in favor of option 2?</p>",
        "id": 492148089,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1736184183
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Using addr_of_mut would require a bunch of annoying casts.</p>",
        "id": 492148215,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1736184233
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Fair enough.</p>",
        "id": 492149153,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1736184491
    },
